OL,3,CDepression and anxiety sufferers 'to
OL,4,Close sickness benefits in welfare
OL,5,Creforms'
OL,7,FDescribing the reforms as "probably
OL,8,Fthe most fundamental reforms in a
OL,9,Fgeneration", he said: "There are those
OL,10,Fthat have perhaps milder mental health
OL,11,Fconditions, or where perhaps there has
OL,12,Fbeen too great a move towards
OL,13,Flabelling certain behaviours as having
OL,14,Fcertain (medical) conditions attached
OL,15,Fto them, where actually work is the
OL,16,Fanswer or part of the answer.
OL,18,F"What we've got to avoid is being in a
OL,19,Fsituation where we too readily say,
OL,20,F'Well, actually, we need you to be on
OL,21,Fbenefits'."
